{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "President Obama wants territorial taxation, in which companies pay tax on their income only where they earn it, and Republicans agree.", "abstract": "The Upshot; shift in focus in national debate over corporate tax policy is due in large part to fact that most egregious form of tax avoidance comes from companies declaring large portions of their income are made in countries offering tax shelters; Pres Obama's proposal for reforming tax code calls for territorial taxation, which would address this form of avoidance, is one of few he has made that has Republican support.", "section_name": "The Upshot", "print_page": "3", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Josh", "role": "reported", "lastname": "BARRO", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By JOSH BARRO"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/05/upshot/corporate-tax-reform-focusing-on-where-the-money-is-not-where-the-jobs-are.html", "lead_paragraph": "President Obama wants territorial taxation, in which companies pay tax on their income only where they earn it, and Republicans agree.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Tax Reform With Focus on Where Money Is", "main": "Corporate Tax Reform: Focusing on Where the Money Is, Not Where the Jobs Are", "content_kicker": "Tax Policy", "kicker": "The Upshot"}, "_id": "54d1a8c838f0d86a52397b7b", "word_count": "802", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/02/04/upshot/04UP-CorpTax1/04UP-CorpTax1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/02/04/upshot/04UP-CorpTax1/04UP-CorpTax1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 376, "url": "images/2015/02/04/upshot/04UP-CorpTax1/04UP-CorpTax1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/02/04/upshot/04UP-CorpTax1/04UP-CorpTax1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "376"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 7